Status monitor:

This is a simple component that can monitor the state of one or more
PEIS components and output an updating timeline for visualization by
the tupleview. It relies on the EasyTimeline format of tupleview for
the actual visualization.

To compile this template:

run "cmake .", then run "make".

To use it, do:

status_monitor --monitor <heading1> <id1> <name1> --monitor <heading2> <id2> <name2>  ...

This will create a timeline with the labels heading1, heading2, ... on
separate rows and with the corresponding values/timepoints of the
tuples id1:name1 id2:name2 etc. 

